We‚Äôre ONE MONTH AWAY from the school holidays! What is on your to-do list with your child? üìí
&nbsp;&nbsp;
To raise awareness on the issue of bullying, Singapore Children‚Äôs Society has collaborated with the National Heritage Board to present Scribble Town, an interactive exhibition for children aged between 9 and 12. By embarking on a quest alongside characters Sam, Dan and Lydia, to save the fictional world of Scribble Town and bring colour back into their world, visitors will be prompted to reflect on their own experiences of bullying, whether they have been victims of bullying themselves or have acted in ways that count as bullying through the interactive elements at each station.&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;
The exhibition is held at the Sun Yat Sen Nanyang Memorial Hall from now till 31 January 2021. SEE YOU THERE!&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;
For more information on bullying, visit www.bullyfree.sg. Together we can create a #bullyfreesg

